#import/clean datasets

#emissions data
CO2_state <- read_excel(here("data/emission_annual.xlsx")) |> 
             clean_names() |> 
             filter(producer_type == "Total Electric Power Industry", 
                    energy_source == "All Sources", state != "US-TOTAL") |> 
             select(year, state, producer_type, energy_source, co2_metric_tons)

CO2_total <- read_excel(here("data/emission_annual.xlsx")) |> 
             clean_names() |> 
             filter(producer_type == "Total Electric Power Industry", 
                    energy_source == "All Sources", state == "US-TOTAL") |> 
             select(year, state, producer_type, energy_source, co2_metric_tons)

#fossil fuel data
fossil_energy <- read_excel(here("data/fossil_energy.xlsx"), 
                            range = "A6:G16", col_names = F) |> 
                 rename(year = 1, coal = 2, petroleum_liquids = 3,
                        petroleum_coke = 4, natural_gas = 5, other_gas = 6, 
                        nuclear = 7) |> 
                 mutate(year = as.integer(year), 
                        total = rowSums(across(where(is.numeric))))
                 
#energy totals by year
energy_year <- read_excel(here("data/renewable_energy.xlsx"), 
                          range = cell_rows(6:16), col_names = F) |> 
               rename(year = 1, wind = 2, solar_photovoltaic = 3, 
                      solar_thermal = 4, wood_fuels = 5, landfill_gas = 6, 
                      biogenic_waste = 7, other_biomass = 8, geothermal = 9, 
                      hydroelectric = 10, total_utility_level = 11, 
                      small_photo_solar = 12, total_photo_solar = 13, 
                      total_solar = 14) |> 
               mutate(small_photo_solar = as.numeric(small_photo_solar), 
                      total_photo_solar = as.numeric(total_photo_solar),
                      total_solar = as.numeric(total_solar)) 

#replace n/a in energy totals
energy_year[is.na(energy_year)] <- 0

#energy by month for 2020
energy_2020 <- read_excel(here("data/renewable_energy.xlsx"),
                          range = cell_rows(17:29)) |> 
               rename(month = 1, wind = 2, solar_photovoltaic = 3, 
                      solar_thermal = 4, wood_fuels = 5, landfill_gas = 6, 
                      biogenic_waste = 7, other_biomass = 8, geothermal = 9, 
                      hydroelectric = 10, total_utility_level = 11, 
                      small_photo_solar = 12, total_photo_solar = 13, 
                      total_solar = 14)

#energy by month for 2021
energy_2021 <- read_excel(here("data/renewable_energy.xlsx"),
                          range = cell_rows(30:42)) |> 
               rename(month = 1, wind = 2, solar_photovoltaic = 3, 
                      solar_thermal = 4, wood_fuels = 5, landfill_gas = 6, 
                      biogenic_waste = 7, other_biomass = 8, geothermal = 9, 
                      hydroelectric = 10, total_utility_level = 11, 
                      small_photo_solar = 12, total_photo_solar = 13, 
                      total_solar = 14)

#energy by month for 2022
energy_2022 <- read_excel(here("data/renewable_energy.xlsx"),
                          range = cell_rows(43:55)) |> 
               rename(month = 1, wind = 2, solar_photovoltaic = 3, 
                      solar_thermal = 4, wood_fuels = 5, landfill_gas = 6, 
                      biogenic_waste = 7, other_biomass = 8, geothermal = 9, 
                      hydroelectric = 10, total_utility_level = 11, 
                      small_photo_solar = 12, total_photo_solar = 13, 
                      total_solar = 14)
#export cleaned data for use in model creation
write.csv(energy_year, file = here("data/energy_year.csv"), row.names = F)

write.csv(energy_2020, file = here("data/energy_2020.csv"), row.names = F)

write.csv(energy_2021, file = here("data/energy_2021.csv"), row.names = F)

write.csv(energy_2022, file = here("data/energy_2022.csv"), row.names = F)
#setting up energy data for plots
energy_year_plot <- energy_year |> 
                    group_by(year) |> 
                    pivot_longer(names_to = "type", values_to = "t_megawatts", cols = 2:14) |> 
                    ungroup() |> 
                    filter(type != "total_photo_solar", type != "total_solar", 
                           type != "total_utility_level")

energy_year_total <- energy_year |> 
                     group_by(year) |> 
                     pivot_longer(names_to = "type", values_to = "t_megawatts", cols = 2:14) |> 
                     ungroup() |> 
                     filter(type == "total_utility_level")
#graph of CO2 emissions
ggplot() +
  geom_line(data = CO2_total, aes(x = year, y = co2_metric_tons)) +
  theme_bw() +
  labs(x = "Year", y = "CO2 Emissions (Metric Tons)",
       title = "Figure 3: CO2 Emissions in Metric Tons from 1990 - 2021") +
  scale_y_continuous(labels = scales::comma) 

#exporting figure
ggsave("plot_3.png", path = here("figs/"))
## Saving 7 x 5 in image
#Plot for renewable energy production total
ggplot() +
  geom_line(data = energy_year_total, aes(x = year, y = t_megawatts), color = "green") +
  geom_line(data = fossil_energy, aes(x = year, y = total/3), color = "red") +
  geom_label(data = energy_year_total, aes(x = c(2019), y = c(800000), label = c("Renewable"))) +
  geom_label(data = energy_year_total, aes(x = c(2019), y = c(1050000), label = c("Fossil"))) +
  labs(x = "Year", y = "Renewable Energy Production (Thousands of MWh)", 
       title = "Figure 1: Total Renewable vs. Fossil Energy Production 2012 - 2022") +
  theme_bw() +
  scale_y_continuous(labels = scales::comma, 
                     sec.axis = sec_axis(~.*3, name = "Fossil Energy Production (Thousands MWh)", 
                                         labels = scales::comma)) +
  scale_x_continuous(labels = c(2012, 2015, 2017, 2020, 2022)) 

#exporting figure
ggsave("plot_1.png", path = here("figs/"))
## Saving 7 x 5 in image
#Plot for renewable energy production by sector
ggplot() +
  geom_line(data = energy_year_plot, aes(x = year, y = t_megawatts, colour = type)) +
  labs(x = "Year", y = "Energy Production (Thousands of MWh)", 
       title = "Figure 2: Renewable Energy Production by Sector 2012 - 2022") +
  theme_bw() +
  scale_x_continuous(labels = c(2012, 2015, 2017, 2020, 2022)) +
  scale_y_continuous(labels = scales::comma) +
  scale_colour_discrete(labels = c("Biogenic Waste", "Geothermal", "Hydroelectric",
                                 "Landfill Gas", "Other Biomass", 
                                 "Small Scale Solar", "Photovoltaic Solar",
                                 "Solar Thermal", "Wind", "Wood Fuels"),
                        name = "Type of Renewable") 

#exporting figure
ggsave("plot_2.png", path = here("figs/"))
